replies.bodyText:
I found it's difficult to apply a common method for Java and JVMTI Agent code because Object and Word are two incompatible systems. I tried to extract the algorithm into the following code:
public class SerializationChecksumCalculator<T> {
    public long calculate(String targetConstructorClassName,
                                String serializationClassName,
                                T serializationClass,
                                Function<T, Long> calculateFromComputeDefaultSUID,
                                Function<T, String> getClassName,
                                Function<T, T> getSuperClass
    ) {
        long checksum = 0L;
        if (targetConstructorClassName != null && targetConstructorClassName.length() > 0) {
            String currentClassName = serializationClassName;
            T currentClass = serializationClass;
            while (!targetConstructorClassName.equals(currentClassName)) {
                long classSUID = calculateFromComputeDefaultSUID.apply(currentClass);
                checksum = checksum * 31 + classSUID;
                currentClass = getSuperClass.apply(currentClass);
                currentClassName = getClassName.apply(currentClass);
            }
            checksum = checksum * 31 + targetConstructorClassName.hashCode();
        }
        return checksum;
    }
}
T is supposed to be Class<?> when it is called from SerializationSupport, and to be JNIObjectHandler when it is called from BreakpointInterceptor. But in fact JNIObjectHandler is Word based and incompatible with Object.

